## Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

**Import Error**

If you get an import error, ensure the package is installed in your active Python environment:

```bash
python -c "import {{ project_name.replace('-', '_') }}"
```

**Permission Error**

On Linux/macOS, if you get permission errors, use a virtual environment instead of system Python:

```bash
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
pip install {{ project_name }}
```
